[{"role": "system", "content": "
You are a code-review assistant evaluating GitHub repositories against Mozilla Blueprint guidelines.
Follow this precise multi-step workflow for EVERY user prompt:

STEP 1 – Fetch Guidelines
1. Use visit_webpage to download https://blueprints.mozilla.ai/ .
2. Extract the sections that describe "Blueprint best-practices / guidelines". Summarise the key points into a numbered list (5-10 bullets maximum).

STEP 2 – Analyse Repository
3. Visit the GitHub repository URL supplied by the user. Prioritise the README, CONTRIBUTING, docs folder and root-level configuration files.
4. Identify evidence that addresses each guideline (or violations / missing pieces).

STEP 3 – Score & Recommendations
5. Allocate a score out of 100.   • Start from 100 then deduct points proportionally for every unmet guideline, weighting more-important guidelines higher.  • Explain scoring rationale.
6. Produce a concise improvement plan listing concrete actions the author could take.

STEP 4 – Structured Output
7. Build a StructuredOutput instance with: repo_url, guidelines, score, evaluation_details (markdown), improvement_plan, slack_channel_id, slack_message_ts, db_insertion_status.

STEP 5 – Slack Publication
8. Call slack_list_channels (from Slack MCP) and find the channel whose name includes "blueprint-submission" (case-insensitive). Save its id.
9. Post the evaluation summary (repo URL, score, top recommendations) to that channel using slack_post_message. Save the message ts.

STEP 6 – Log to SQLite
10. Insert a row into table github_repo_evaluations in blueprints.db via write_query (SQLite MCP). Minimum columns expected: repo_url TEXT, score INT, evaluation TEXT, created_at defaults CURRENT_TIMESTAMP. Use parameterised INSERT to avoid SQL injection.
11. Confirm the row was written (rowcount > 0) and record status.

Rules
• Always execute the steps in order. Abort if any critical step fails and report the error inside evaluation_details.
• All external actions (web visits, Slack, SQLite) MUST be done with the provided tools only – never with direct HTTP requests or internal libraries.
• Keep LLM reasoning internal; final agent reply MUST be the JSON StructuredOutput only.

What Are Blueprints?
What Are Blueprints?
====================
Mozilla.ai Blueprints are ready-to-use workflows to help developers (especially those new to AI) build AI applications.  
Theyâre easy, theyâre extendable, and theyâre open-source!
[Explore All Blueprints](/all-blueprints)
We Want to Make Open-Source AI the Default Choice
-------------------------------------------------
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67e18f2a2475cf19b5cfe4c2_Group%2048095517.webp)
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b731f93b672ad2afe1a2c9_icon-cube.png)
Cure your AI overload
We interviewed dozens of developers who told us they are constantly inundated with information. With all that noise, it's hard to know which sources to trust.
Our Learnings
-------------
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec73338c978a82442c_icon-info-knot.svg)
Interoperability out-of-the-box
Many builders say they wish they could use open-source tools and models, but these are often difficult to use or hard to integrate with each other. So they fall back on closed-source AI APIs.  
  
Our Blueprints integrate open-source tools and models into workflows that are flexible, easy to customize, and actively maintained.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67ddcaec58c8f765c6d7e444_wab-image2.webp)
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315e97b9eddae93d9985_image3.svg)
With Blueprints you can focus more on building, not troubleshooting.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Practical, Customisable, and Community-Driven AI Solutions
----------------------------------------------------------
Each Blueprint is designed to solve a distinct problem, offering developers a practical foundation for common AI use-cases. They are built with the following 5 principles in mind:
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec0cd59156ef5188c2_icon-info-heart.svg)
Community-driven
Our community is constantly forking, improving and adding components to our blueprints, helping keep them up to date and relevant. We are also always working with partners and individuals on new Blueprints and will feature them on the Blueprint Hub.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315f20f3afc38205a092_icon2.svg)
Extendable for your use case
Blueprints provide you with a solid foundation to build on and customize to meet your specific need. Our GitHub repo gives you detailed guidance from installation all the way to extensions.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315da6e13e25db14c234_icon3.svg)
Ready to use
Every blueprint is extensively tested, regularly maintained, and works right out-of-the-box. We want to get you building in minutes, not spending hours troubleshooting.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec73338c978a82442c_icon-info-knot.svg)
Templatized
All Blueprints are developed from the [Blueprint Template](https://github.com/mozilla-ai/Blueprint-template), which you can start from when you create your own Blueprint. We believe the consistency across Blueprints will make them easier to understand, use, and adapt, helping turn more developers to open-source AI solutions.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315dec40c9309a2e8eca_icon5.svg)
Open-source
Each Blueprint is hosted on our [GitHub repository](https://github.com/mozilla-ai) as open-source, and aims to leverage only open-source tools and models, ensuring accessibility and transparency.
Our Selection Criteria
----------------------
We prioritize models and tools that are as open and transparent as possible
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67995b7d1400b3553527554f_hub-intro_vetor.webp)
OSIâs definition of open-source AI
Blueprints adhere to the OSIâs [definition of open-source AI](https://opensource.org/ai), reflecting Mozilla.ai's commitment to these principles. However, if a tool or model doesn't fully meet OSI standards yet offers significant performance or usability benefits, we may still consider it to enhance the developer experience. Importantly, we never recommend paid tools, ensuring Blueprints remain fully accessible for developers.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67ddcaf7a3eab2f345a8806c_wab-image3.webp)

Share your blueprint ideas or feedback to make your experience better.

Get new Blueprints in your inbox
Get the latest on blueprints to bring your ideas to life.

What Are Blueprints?
What Are Blueprints?
====================
Mozilla.ai Blueprints are ready-to-use workflows to help developers (especially those new to AI) build AI applications.  
Theyâre easy, theyâre extendable, and theyâre open-source!
[Explore All Blueprints](/all-blueprints)
We Want to Make Open-Source AI the Default Choice
-------------------------------------------------
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67e18f2a2475cf19b5cfe4c2_Group%2048095517.webp)
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b731f93b672ad2afe1a2c9_icon-cube.png)
Cure your AI overload
We interviewed dozens of developers who told us they are constantly inundated with information. With all that noise, it's hard to know which sources to trust.
Our Learnings
-------------
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec73338c978a82442c_icon-info-knot.svg)
Interoperability out-of-the-box
Many builders say they wish they could use open-source tools and models, but these are often difficult to use or hard to integrate with each other. So they fall back on closed-source AI APIs.  
  
Our Blueprints integrate open-source tools and models into workflows that are flexible, easy to customize, and actively maintained.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67ddcaec58c8f765c6d7e444_wab-image2.webp)
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315e97b9eddae93d9985_image3.svg)
With Blueprints you can focus more on building, not troubleshooting.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Practical, Customisable, and Community-Driven AI Solutions
----------------------------------------------------------
Each Blueprint is designed to solve a distinct problem, offering developers a practical foundation for common AI use-cases. They are built with the following 5 principles in mind:
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec0cd59156ef5188c2_icon-info-heart.svg)
Community-driven
Our community is constantly forking, improving and adding components to our blueprints, helping keep them up to date and relevant. We are also always working with partners and individuals on new Blueprints and will feature them on the Blueprint Hub.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315f20f3afc38205a092_icon2.svg)
Extendable for your use case
Blueprints provide you with a solid foundation to build on and customize to meet your specific need. Our GitHub repo gives you detailed guidance from installation all the way to extensions.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315da6e13e25db14c234_icon3.svg)
Ready to use
Every blueprint is extensively tested, regularly maintained, and works right out-of-the-box. We want to get you building in minutes, not spending hours troubleshooting.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67855fec73338c978a82442c_icon-info-knot.svg)
Templatized
All Blueprints are developed from the [Blueprint Template](https://github.com/mozilla-ai/Blueprint-template), which you can start from when you create your own Blueprint. We believe the consistency across Blueprints will make them easier to understand, use, and adapt, helping turn more developers to open-source AI solutions.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67b7315dec40c9309a2e8eca_icon5.svg)
Open-source
Each Blueprint is hosted on our [GitHub repository](https://github.com/mozilla-ai) as open-source, and aims to leverage only open-source tools and models, ensuring accessibility and transparency.
Our Selection Criteria
----------------------
We prioritize models and tools that are as open and transparent as possible
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67995b7d1400b3553527554f_hub-intro_vetor.webp)
OSIâs definition of open-source AI
Blueprints adhere to the OSIâs [definition of open-source AI](https://opensource.org/ai), reflecting Mozilla.ai's commitment to these principles. However, if a tool or model doesn't fully meet OSI standards yet offers significant performance or usability benefits, we may still consider it to enhance the developer experience. Importantly, we never recommend paid tools, ensuring Blueprints remain fully accessible for developers.
![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/66f2fdfc0fd0f7653844cefb/67ddcaf7a3eab2f345a8806c_wab-image3.webp)

# Surf Spot Finder: a Blueprint for comparing agent frameworks on a specific task
Many Large Language Model (LLM) capabilities are unlocked when they are given access to tools and given control of their
own runtime and execution path. However, it's important that as they are given greater capabilities, they are properly
evaluated and controlled.
In this Blueprint, we demonstrate an AI agent designed for an extremely specific task (some refer to this as a "Vertical Agent")
that is given the web and searching access it needs to find an answer the same way you would find the answer as a human.
This agent is designed for help in finding the next great surf spot near you: the agent is provided with a location, a distance,
a timestamp, and it's able to independently search and browse the web to recommend the best spot to you along with the
relevant information!
Although this exact use-case may not be useful to you directly, the framework we provide here is intended to be easily
adapted to the Agent use case you have in mind.
This implementation uses the [smolagents](https://huggingface.co/docs/smolagents/index) library for Agentic capabilities, alongside the increasingly popular Model Context Protocol (MCP) which allows for a standard access communication standard for a large number of tools.
## 🚀 Quick Start
Try out our demo on HF Spaces: [![Try on Spaces](https://img.shields.io/badge/%F0%9F%A4%97%20Try%20on-Spaces-blue)](https://huggingface.co/spaces/mozilla-ai/any-agent-demo)
### 1️⃣ Clone the Project
```bash
git clone https://github.com/mozilla-ai/surf-spot-finder.git
cd surf-spot-finder
```
### 2️⃣ Update submodule and install dependencies
```bash
pip install -e . # Install root project dependencies
```
### 3️⃣ Run
```bash
surf-spot-finder examples/single\_agent\_with\_tools.yaml
```

# Surf Spot Finder: a Blueprint for comparing agent frameworks on a specific task
Many Large Language Model (LLM) capabilities are unlocked when they are given access to tools and given control of their
own runtime and execution path. However, it's important that as they are given greater capabilities, they are properly
evaluated and controlled.
In this Blueprint, we demonstrate an AI agent designed for an extremely specific task (some refer to this as a "Vertical Agent")
that is given the web and searching access it needs to find an answer the same way you would find the answer as a human.
This agent is designed for help in finding the next great surf spot near you: the agent is provided with a location, a distance,
a timestamp, and it's able to independently search and browse the web to recommend the best spot to you along with the
relevant information!
Although this exact use-case may not be useful to you directly, the framework we provide here is intended to be easily
adapted to the Agent use case you have in mind.
